The paper discusses the implementation and performance of a new I/O model for scientific applications, which is a topic that falls under several CS sub-categories. Distributed computing (cs.DC) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on the Distributed Asynchronous Object Storage (DAOS) technology. The paper also discusses the HDF5 library, which is an I/O library for scientific applications, making categories such as databases (cs.DB), scientific computing (cs.SC), and data structures (cs.DS) likely as well. Finally, the paper discusses fault tolerance and efficiency, which are topics that fall under software engineering (cs.SE).
